<P><FONT FACE="AGaramond" SIZE=4><B>Course requirements:</B> For everyone, reading and attending class to discuss the
  course materials and a take-home final exam
  (out at the end of the ninth week, due at the start of finals week). For those who want a letter grade (rather than SU), a term project on a computer law topic of your choice,
  presented orally (half talk, half discussion); we will take signups for these in Week 2. </FONT></p>
<P><FONT FACE="AGaramond" SIZE=4><B><A HREF="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~kay/courses/269/s10readings.html">Readings:</A></B> I&#39;ll assign readings as we go.  Most will be on-line; I'll arrange access to the others.  The course home page is </FONT><FONT FACE="Courier New"><A HREF="http://www.ics.uci.edu/~kay/courses/269/">http://www.ics.uci.edu/~kay/courses/269/</A></FONT><FONT FACE="AGaramond" SIZE=4>.
